The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | ECB confirms Stanford talks
                                                                                                                                                                                                     ECB confirms Stanford talks
            A STAFF REPORTER                       
	Calcutta: The England and Wales Cricket Board (ECB) on Tuesday confirmed that a meeting had been held with Sir Allen Stanford in the full knowledge of the West Indies Cricket Board.         
	The meetings, which were held in London, were described as very positive and constructive and were in line with the ECBs strategic approach towards Twenty20 cricket, according to a release.         
	ECB has also confirmed that in accordance with decisions taken by the ICC  and supported by both the BCCI and ECB  that the Future Tours Programme takes precedence over domestic competitions.                                                                                                                          
